VALUES
(42, 12, 28, 40, 14, 31, 31, 'O ye of little faith', 'Connection of Little Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''O ye of little faith,'' highlighting a theme of doubt and trust in God''s provision. The context in Luke addresses worry about material needs, while Matthew illustrates doubt in a moment of crisis.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 28, 40, 6, 30, 30, 'O ye of little faith', 'Clothing of the Grass', 'Both passages emphasize God''s provision for His creation, specifically mentioning how He clothes the grass of the field. The phrase ''O ye of little faith'' appears in both, highlighting a call to trust in God''s care.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 28, 42, 8, 25, 25, 'O ye of little faith', 'Faith and God''s Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of faith in God''s care and power. In Luke 12:28, Jesus reassures His followers of God''s provision, while in Luke 8:25, He questions their faith amidst a storm, demonstrating His authority over nature.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 28, 60, 1, 24, 24, 'grass', 'Connection of Grass Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the transience of grass, illustrating the fleeting nature of life. Luke highlights God''s care for creation, while Peter reflects on the impermanence of human glory compared to divine provision.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 29, 40, 6, 31, 31, NULL, 'Concern for Daily Needs', 'Both passages emphasize not worrying about basic necessities like food and drink. They encourage a focus away from anxiety regarding material needs.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 29, 42, 12, 22, 22, NULL, 'Concern for Daily Needs', 'Both passages emphasize not worrying about daily necessities like food and clothing. They encourage a focus away from material concerns, promoting trust in divine provision.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 29, 42, 22, 35, 35, NULL, 'Provision and Trust in God', 'Both passages emphasize reliance on God for needs. In Luke 12:29, the call to avoid worry about food and drink parallels the assurance in Luke 22:35 that lack was not experienced when sent without provisions.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 29, 42, 10, 7, 8, 'what ye shall eat, or what ye shall drink', 'Provision and Trust in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of reliance on God for provision. Both passages emphasize not worrying about food and drink, suggesting a trust in God''s provision while engaging in ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 30, 40, 6, 32, 32, 'your Father knoweth that ye have need of these things', 'Connection of Divine Provision', 'Both passages emphasize that the Father knows the needs of His followers. They highlight the contrast between the concerns of the nations and the assurance of God''s provision.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 30, 40, 6, 8, 8, 'your Father knoweth that ye have need of these things', 'God''s Knowledge of Needs', 'Both passages emphasize that ''your Father knoweth'' the needs of His followers. This connection highlights the assurance that God is aware of what is necessary before they even ask.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 30, 42, 12, 32, 32, 'your Father knoweth that ye have need of these things', 'Divine Provision and Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize God''s knowledge of our needs and His desire to provide for us. The assurance in Luke 12:30 that the Father knows our needs connects to the promise in Luke 12:32 that it is His pleasure to give us the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 30, 49, 4, 17, 17, 'the nations of the world seek after', 'Seeking Needs vs. Vanity', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the nations'' pursuit of material needs and the call for believers to avoid walking in the vanity of their minds. Both passages emphasize the difference in priorities between worldly concerns and spiritual living.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 30, 60, 4, 2, 4, 'your Father knoweth that ye have need of these things', 'Seeking God''s Will vs. Worldly Desires', 'This connection highlights the contrast between seeking the needs known by God and living according to the lusts of men. Both passages emphasize the distinction between divine provision and worldly pursuits.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 30, 52, 4, 5, 5, 'your Father knoweth that ye have need of these things', 'Seeking Needs and Gentile Behavior', 'This connection highlights the contrast between those who seek after worldly needs and the Gentiles who do not know God. Both passages emphasize the differing motivations and understanding of God''s provision among believers and non-believers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 30, 43, 20, 17, 17, 'your Father', 'Father''s Knowledge and Relationship', 'This connection highlights the relationship between God as Father in both passages. In Luke, it emphasizes that God knows our needs, while in John, Jesus refers to God as both His Father and the believers'' Father.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 31, 40, 6, 33, 33, 'seek ye the kingdom of God', 'Seeking the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking the kingdom of God first. They convey a similar message that prioritizing God''s kingdom leads to the provision of other needs.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 31, 58, 13, 5, 5, 'seek ye the kingdom of God', 'Seeking Contentment in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking God''s kingdom and being content with what one has. Both passages encourage reliance on God for provision and emphasize the importance of prioritizing spiritual over material concerns.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 31, 19, 34, 9, 9, NULL, 'Seeking God and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the provision for those who seek and fear the Lord. Luke 12:31 encourages seeking the kingdom of God, while Psalms 34:9 assures that there is no want for those who fear Him.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 31, 11, 3, 11, 13, 'seek ye the kingdom of God', 'Seeking Wisdom and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking understanding and the kingdom of God over material wealth. In 1 Kings, Solomon''s request for wisdom leads to God granting him riches, paralleling Luke''s promise that seeking God''s kingdom results in additional blessings.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 31, 43, 6, 27, 27, 'seek ye the kingdom of God', 'Seeking Eternal Sustenance', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking what is eternal rather than temporary. Luke encourages seeking the kingdom of God, while John contrasts perishable food with everlasting sustenance.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 31, 54, 4, 8, 8, 'seek ye the kingdom of God', 'Seeking God and Profitability', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prioritizing spiritual pursuits over physical ones. Luke highlights seeking the kingdom of God, while 1 Timothy points out that godliness is profitable for both this life and the next.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 31, 19, 84, 11, 11, 'seek ye the kingdom of God', 'Seeking God''s Provision', 'Both passages emphasize God''s provision for those who seek Him. Luke 12:31 encourages seeking the kingdom of God, while Psalms 84:11 assures that no good thing will be withheld from the upright.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 32, 58, 12, 28, 28, 'give you the kingdom', 'Connection of God''s Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s kingdom being given to believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving and serving within this unshakeable kingdom with reverence.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 32, 60, 1, 3, 5, 'give you the kingdom', 'Inheritance and Kingdom Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s promise to His followers. Both passages emphasize the idea of receiving a kingdom and an inheritance, showcasing God''s pleasure in granting these gifts to believers.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 32, 50, 2, 13, 13, 'good pleasure', 'God''s Good Pleasure', 'Both passages emphasize God''s pleasure in giving and working within believers. Luke highlights God''s desire to give the kingdom, while Philippians speaks to God''s work in believers for His good pleasure.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 32, 66, 1, 6, 6, 'your Father’s good pleasure', 'Kingship and Divine Favor', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s intention to elevate His followers. Both passages emphasize the idea of receiving the kingdom and being made kings, reflecting God''s pleasure in granting authority to His people.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 32, 42, 10, 21, 21, 'your Father’s good pleasure', 'Divine Revelation to the Humble', 'Both passages emphasize God''s pleasure in revealing His kingdom to the humble. In Luke 12:32, the ''little flock'' is reassured of their inheritance, while in Luke 10:21, the ''babes'' receive divine truths. This connection highlights God''s favor towards those who are lowly.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 32, 40, 25, 34, 34, NULL, 'Inheritance of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of inheriting the kingdom, with Luke highlighting God''s pleasure in giving it and Matthew depicting the blessed receiving it. This connection highlights the assurance of believers in their inheritance.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 32, 23, 40, 11, 11, 'little flock', 'Shepherding and Divine Care', 'This connection highlights the theme of God as a shepherd who cares for His flock. Both passages emphasize the nurturing aspect of God''s relationship with His people, assuring them of His provision and guidance.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 33, 40, 19, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Treasures in Heaven', 'Both passages emphasize the act of selling possessions and giving to the poor as a means to secure treasure in heaven. This connection highlights the importance of prioritizing spiritual wealth over material wealth.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
